email_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) for o=
ver a decade. Meanwhile, Tesla delivered 495,570 cars in the fourth quarter=
 of 2024, some 12,000 fewer than Wall Street analysts expected.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

And yet, Tesla=E2=80=99s market value is now $1.22 trillion, some $500 bill=
ion more than the market value of
the next 10 largest global automobile companies combined. That=E2=80=99s ri=
ght, more than Toyota, BYD, Porsche, Mercedes, Ferrari, et al. thrown toget=
her.

